-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Groovy
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
- is built on top of java, extends java.
- groovy can be executed directly (groovy command line tool) or compiled to
  bytecode
- supports domain specific languages (DSL) for more readability
- dynamic typing: variables are defined via keyword 'def'

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 dynamic typing
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
- provides greater flexibility for manipulating class properties and
  variables

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
 closure
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
- piece of code wrapped into an object
- can be passed around with a reference
- is executable
- can receive parameters and return value

